Just for some context could you explain/confirm:

Without validation your meeting tool does show up?

With your validation the form is actually submitting to HubSpot? (you can see the submission in HubSpot)

It sounds like the submission isn’t actually happening.

This is the process I do for validation
```window.addEventListener('message', event =&gt; {
   if(event.data.type === 'hsFormCallback' &amp;&amp; event.data.eventName === 'onFormReady') {
    // event listener for submit button on click
       // Do custom validation
          // If validation fails e.preventDefault();
          // If validation succeeds just let it carry on```
Even if someone submits by pressing enter the HubSpot JS seems to trigger the click event anyway

Finally this custom validation will only stop non devs from entering information in the forms. you can easily change the validation JS or just grab the form ID from the page source and submit data with the form submission API

